HEADWORD: Physostomi
<hw>Phy*sos"to*mi</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧*s⟦ocr⟧s"t⟦osl⟧*m⟦imac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>prop. n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>fy^sa</grk> a bellows +
<grk>sto`ma</grk> mouth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
fishes in which the air bladder is provided with a duct, and the ventral
fins, when present, are abdominal. It includes the salmons, herrings,
carps, catfishes, and others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1082 --></p>

<p><ent>Physostomous</ent>⟦br⟧
